        <p rend="right"><date n="1945-07-17" cert="high">July 17, 1945</date></p>

        <p>Dr. <persName key="7721" role="rec">S. Kracauer</persName><lb/>Museum of Modern
          Art<lb/>11 West 53rd Street<lb/><placeName key="49021">New York</placeName>, <placeName
            key="50589">N.Y.</placeName></p>


        <p><emph n="salutation">Dear Dr. <persName key="7721" role="rec"
          >Kracauer</persName></emph>:</p>

        <p>I am leaving this country<note type="reg"><placeName key="49115">Vereinigte Staaten von
              Amerika</placeName></note> for <placeName key="49050">London</placeName> where I will
          attend meetings of the Board of Governors of Hebrew University and of the Actions
          Committee of the World Zionist Organization.</p>

        <p>From <placeName key="49050">London</placeName> I will proceed to <placeName key="49814"
            >Palestine</placeName>, and hope to be back here again for some months late this
          fall.</p>

        <p>I very much regret that I could not see you any more before my departure, but am looking
          forward to meeting you again after my return.</p>

        <p><emph n="salute">With kindest regards</emph>,</p>

        <p rend="right"><emph n="salute">Sincerely yours</emph>,</p>

        <p rend="right"><persName key="73655" role="aut"><hi rendition="other-hand">Salman
            Schocken</hi></persName><lb/><unclear>gz</unclear><note
            type="intern">Wie hier mit der von der Sekretärin gez. Unterschrift umgehen?</note></p>

        <p rend="right"><persName key="73655" role="aut">Salman Schocken</persName></p>

        <p>P.S. This letter was dictated by Mr. <persName key="73655" role="aut">Schocken</persName>
          but written only after he left.</p>

